      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KING OWEN (2) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 4.5 lengths at The Meadows in a handy 29.97 beating Scott Sigma. The form out of last race has been strong. Can continue the winning form. OVERFLOW BEAU (4) made light work of a wide draw last time with a slick early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (29.86) at this track over 520m. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to his name from four starts. Expected to feature again. DIZZY DIGBY (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fifth (30.32) in a Grade 5 at The Gardens. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Has ability and can measure up. BOTH BOWERS ACE (5) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out.",
